          "title": "Data Analytics Engineer",
          "description": "<p>Data Analytics Engineer (Business Intelligence)</p>\n<p>This position will play an important role in transforming data into actionable information by enabling deeper understanding and improvement of business processes. In this role, the individual will assist in analyzing and implementing business intelligence architecture for the organization. Additionally, identifying conclusions from business intelligence initiatives, interacting with a variety of stakeholders, and communicating critical requirements will be essential to help Cognate achieve its organizational goals.\nEDUCATION and EXPERIENCE\nBachelor's degree in IT, Computer Science, Engineering, Finance or related field.\n3+ years of experience in data management, data engineering, visualization, and/or data warehousing\nDATA MANAGEMENT AND ANALYTICS\nExperience with data management and analysis. Skilled in dashboard design and development. Experience in Excel is required. Proficiency in Power BI / Tableau and database technologies such as SQL Server is required. Hands-on experience building, maintaining, and supporting business intelligence data backends, specifically data warehouses.\nExperience with enterprise (Azure, AWS, etc.) or open-source (Apache Spark, Delta Lake, etc.) cloud services preferred.\nSpecific skills consistent with Microsoft technical architecture preferred, including Microsoft BI stack (SSIS, SSAS, SSRS, Power BI, Azure Data Factory)\nAbility to write and develop SQL queries required\nProficiency with DAX measures in Power BI\nData integration, ETL, or ELT experience required\nPython programming experience preferred\nIdeal candidate possesses strong business acumen, project management, and organizational skills</p>\n<p>OTHER SKILLS AND REASONING ABILITY\nAdvanced skills in Office 365 products, especially Power Platform.\nExperience leveraging data to drive decisions in professional or extracurricular endeavors.\nComfortable working independently and collaboratively.\nProven (GitHub, Kaggle, etc.) ability to automate tasks or provide solutions that require a proficiency in programming.\nAbility to understand and use REST APIs\nAbility to comprehend, analyze, and interpret complex data sets.\nAbility to solve problems involving several options and forecast multiple outcomes.\nAdvanced analytical and quantitative aptitude.\nESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITES\nDevelops a deep familiarity with a variety of data sources including transactional databases, data warehouses, internal tools, and external integrations.\nCollaborate in the deployment of reporting and dashboard solutions\nParticipate in design, development, and analysis of data architecture and warehousing approaches\nUse effective data visualization techniques to communicate information clearly and efficiently\nWork to ensure the quality, accuracy, and integrity of data\nBuild, implement, support BI solutions\nTest, monitor, manage, and validate BI activity including data extraction, transformation, movement, loading, cleansing, and updating processes\nDevelop BI databases\nDemonstrate knowledge of enterprise source systems and database schemas\nBuild and maintain tabular models\nDevelop measures for aggregate analysis of production metrics\nPerform varying methods of data analysis\nParticipate in the development of consistent data definitions and use\nCreation of data / process flow documentation\nParticipate in developing and upholding data management and governance strategies\nDemonstrates a self-directed approach to departmental responsibilities\nDemonstrates the ability to deal with pressure to meet deadlines, to be accurate, and to handle constantly changing situations.\nAccepts additional projects and responsibilities as assigned\nDemonstrates capacity to deal with a variety of people and engage others in a cooperative and collaborative workspace\nCommitment to continuous education and exposure to modern tools and techniques\nContribute project deliverables to business intelligence projects internal groups.\nReview project deliverables including Power BI dashboards, formal reports, PowerPoint briefings, etc.\nAssist presentations (both in-person or virtually) of project progress meetings and presentations of results.\nProblem solve technical issues and answer internal stakeholder questions. Escalate issues to supervisor and dedicated technical resources as needed.\nRigorous review and improvement of project processes.\nProvide subject matter expertise on data-related processes and analyses.\nCreate, maintain and optimize creative data visualizations and dashboards (primarily in Power BI) to derive actionable intelligence.\nAggregation and analysis of quantitative data; forecast and trending of performance data.\nDevelop and refine cost models for licensing requirements of the organization</p>\n<p>“Cognate BioServices provides equal employment opportunities to all employees and qualified applicants for employment and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any type without regard to race, color, religion, age, sex, national origin, disability status, genetics, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state or local laws.\nThis policy applies to all terms and conditions of employment, including recruiting, hiring, placement, promotion, termination, layoff, recall, transfer, leaves of absence, compensation and training.”</p>\n",
          "how_to_apply": "<p><a href=\"http://www.cognatebioservices.com/recruitment\">www.cognatebioservices.com/recruitment</a></p>\n<p>Questions?\nContact <a href=\"mailto:recruitment@cognatebioservices.com\">recruitment@cognatebioservices.com</a>.</p>\n<p>With Enthusiasm,\nCognate BioServices Recruitment Team</p>\n",
